  "text": "HLA-DRB1 genotyping. We previously reported that there was a relationship between selective expansion of T-cells that bear TCRBV2 and TCRBV6S5 subfamilies in vivo and HLA-DRB1*0901 in patients with KD [CITATION_1] and after in vitro stimulation of PBMC with SPE-C (16). In the present study, we carried out HLA-DRB1 genotyping to determine the dominant DRB1 genotype among patients with KD. The frequencies of DRB1 in 56 patients with KD and healthy adults in the Kansai area are shown in Table 4 . The frequencies of the DRB1*04051, 0406, and 0901 were higher, whereas that of 1101 was lower in patients with KD as compared with the healthy adults.",
